<p>I am parsing an email body text, and I have this in the source of the email:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Questo dominio =E8 aperto e operativo da diversi anni, non riesco a =   capire l=92esigenza e cosa =E8 cambiato.=20</p> </blockquote>  <p>I know the client used the charset iso-8859-1. I also know that <code>"\xE8"</code> in iso-8859-1 is the charter <code>"é"</code> in utf-8:</p>  <pre><code>"\xE8".encode "UTF-8", "ISO-8859-1" # =&gt; "è" </code></pre>  <p>Why do I find <code>"=E8"</code> instead of <code>"\xE8"</code>?</p>